glosses: Abbreviation of iltapäivällä (“after noon, in the evening, post meridiem”); pm, p.m.

alt_of.extra: (“after noon, in the evening, post meridiem”); pm, p.m.

words.etymology_text: Possibly of sound-symbolic origin; many variants are found in dialects, such as ipale, ipara, ipare, ipero, iprake. Compare also pipana.

forms.form: Rare. Only used with substantive adjectives.

words.etymology_text: Internationalism (see English ipsilateral). Adapted with the adjectival suffix + -inen.
